uded in this unique study, anyone interested in American history and American Studies will find it as appealing as will students and scholars of American music.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aMusicxHistory and criticismxUnited StatesxUnited States. 0aMusiczUnited StatesxHistory and criticism. 4aGeneral. 4aMusic. 7aMUSIC / General.2bisacsh1 aCrawford, Richard, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt0 cprintz978052022482740uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052092545840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520925458423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520925458/original  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles